The Hand-Engraved Micropavé at $1,600 with 87 reviews is the strongest vintage-romantic option in the rose gold catalog at this price point. Hand-engraving on a rose gold shank creates surface texture that catches light at the shoulders — in combination with a pear center diamond, the engraved shoulder detail draws the eye from stone to setting and back, creating a ring that reads as crafted rather than commercial. The Floral Side Stone by James Allen ($3,895) is the most ornate rose gold setting available for pear diamonds on Blue Nile — floral motifs in rose gold are the closest off-the-shelf approximation of original Art Nouveau jewelry design.

